---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Founders — SproutForge3D">
  <section class="section">
    <h1 class="h1">Founders</h1>
    <p class="lead">We’re a small, classroom‑obsessed team building better tools for learning biology — starting with DNA and RNA kits that actually feel good to use.</p>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1.5rem">

      <!-- Esteban -->
      <article class="card">
        <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:center">
          <div style="width:84px;height:84px;border-radius:16px;background:var(--pastel-blue)"></div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="h2" style="margin:0">Esteban Gardea — Co‑founder</h2>
            <p class="muted" style="margin:.15rem 0 0">Biochemical engineering @ ASU • Head of 3‑D & product design</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top:.75rem">
          Esteban brings an invention‑first mindset to our kits. He prototypes fast, listens to teacher feedback, and iterates until
          the parts snap together cleanly and the activity “clicks.” His background spans biotechnologies, molecular sciences,
          teaching, and 3‑D printing — the mix that turns classroom pain points into solid, durable parts.
        </p>
        <p>
          He leads our geometry and tolerance work: base pairing that’s obvious but precise, strand direction that’s visible,
          and components that survive real classroom handling.
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3" style="margin-top:.5rem">
          <a class="btn-ghost" href="#" aria-label="LinkedIn (Esteban)">LinkedIn</a>
          <a class="btn-ghost" href="mailto:sproutforged@gmail.com" aria-label="Email (Esteban)">Email</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Preston -->
      <article class="card">
        <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;align-items:center">
          <div style="width:84px;height:84px;border-radius:16px;background:var(--pastel-green)"></div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="h2" style="margin:0">Preston Roser — Co‑founder</h2>
            <p class="muted" style="margin:.15rem 0 0">Computer Science @ ASU • Curriculum, software & outreach</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top:.75rem">
          Preston focuses on learning experience. He turns complex concepts into clear steps, writes teacher‑ready guides,
          and builds the software that supports downloads, updates, and educator community. He’s passionate about access —
          getting high‑quality materials into more classrooms, for less.
        </p>
        <p>
          Strengths include product storytelling, educator interviews, and building the tiny details that reduce prep time.
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3" style="margin-top:.5rem">
          <a class="btn-ghost" href="#" aria-label="LinkedIn (Preston)">LinkedIn</a>
          <a class="btn-ghost" href="#" aria-label="GitHub (Preston)">GitHub</a>
          <a class="btn-ghost" href="mailto:sproutforged@gmail.com" aria-label="Email (Preston)">Email</a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="margin-top:1.25rem">
      <p class="muted" style="margin:0">
        Operating as <strong>SproutForge3D LLC</strong> while we continue to refine our naming. Find us on Instagram at <strong>@sproutforged</strong> or email
        <a href="mailto:sproutforged@gmail.com">sproutforged@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

